---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="MangaRead // Yanis Amani"
  description="A Rust-powered manga reading platform with automatic scraping, merging, and a web interface."
  lang="en"
>
  <section class="project-hero" data-animate>
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/#projects" class="project-back">← Back to Projects</a>
      <span class="project-cat">Web Application</span>
      <div class="accent-rule"></div>
      <h1 class="project-title">MangaRead</h1>
      <p class="project-tagline">A manga reader that scrapes chapters from third-party sites, merges them into series, and serves them through a web interface.</p>
      <div class="project-links">
        <a href="https://github.com/DevYatsu/mangaread" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn-primary">View on GitHub →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="project-section" data-animate>
    <div class="container project-section-inner">
      <div class="project-sidebar">
        <span class="project-sidebar-label">Tech Stack</span>
        <div class="project-techs">
          <a href="https://rust-lang.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="tech-tag">Rust</a>
          <a href="https://docs.rs/axum" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="tech-tag">Axum</a>
          <a href="https://sqlite.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="tech-tag">SQLite</a>
          <a href="https://docker.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="tech-tag">Docker</a>
          <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="tech-tag">HTML/CSS/JS</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="project-content">
        <h2>What it does</h2>
        <p>MangaRead scrapes manga chapters from third-party scanlation sites, merges them into unified series entries, and serves everything through a local web interface. You can bookmark series, track reading progress, and the server auto-syncs new chapters in the background.</p>

        <h2>Architecture</h2>
        <p>Three Rust crates in one workspace:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>mangaread-core</strong> — domain types, SQLite repository, series merging logic</li>
          <li><strong>scraper</strong> — SiteAdapter trait with per-site implementations (Demonicscans, Manhuaplus), CLI binary + library</li>
          <li><strong>website</strong> — Axum web server with 10 route modules, Maud templates, static assets</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The database uses SQLite with WAL mode. Four tables: series, manga, chapters, pages. All inserts use <code>ON CONFLICT ... DO UPDATE</code> so the whole thing is safe to re-run.</p>
        <p>Chapters from different sources get linked to one unified series by normalized title. If two sources have the same chapter, the one with the most pages wins.</p>

		<pre class="mermaid">flowchart TB
    CLI[ScraperEngine] --> DB[(SQLite)]
    WEB[Axum Server] --> DB
    WEB <--> BROWSER[Browser]
    BROWSER --> JS[app.js + localStorage]</pre>

        <pre class="mermaid">
erDiagram
    SERIES ||--o&#123; MANGA : contains
    MANGA ||--o&#123; CHAPTER : has
    CHAPTER ||--o&#123; PAGE : contains

    SERIES &#123;
        int id PK
        string title
        string normalized_title UK
        string description
    &#125;

    MANGA &#123;
        int id PK
        int series_id FK
        string source
        string source_url
        string title
    &#125;

    CHAPTER &#123;
        int id PK
        int manga_id FK
        int number
        string title
        int page_count
        string source
    &#125;

    PAGE &#123;
        int id PK
        int chapter_id FK
        int page_number
        string image_url
    &#125;
        </pre>

        <h2>The hard parts</h2>
        <p><strong>Chromedriver.</strong> The scraper uses a real browser to render JavaScript-heavy manga sites. Getting chromedriver to behave consistently in Docker was easily 30% of the development time. Headless mode, sandbox issues, zombie processes — the usual webdriver horror show.</p>
        <p><strong>SQLite and threading.</strong> rusqlite's Connection is not Sync, so each scraper thread opens its own connection. The main AppState wraps its connection in a Mutex. This sounds simple, but the borrow checker had opinions.</p>
        <p><strong>Client-side state without accounts.</strong> No authentication, no database sessions. Bookmarks and reading progress live entirely in localStorage. This means the JavaScript reads from localStorage and builds the DOM via a tiny h() helper. It's surprisingly clean but debugging state is harder when you can't just query a database.</p>

        <h2>What I learned</h2>
        <p>This was my first real Rust project with multiple workspace crates, and it taught me more than any tutorial. I learned that Rust's type system is incredible for domain modeling (no invalid states possible) but also that fighting the borrow checker for the 50th time at 2am is a rite of passage.</p>
        <p>The scraper adapter pattern (trait + per-site implementations) taught me that good abstractions pay off immediately when you add a second source. The sync loop design (background thread, 6-hour interval, parallel scraping) taught me about Tokio channels and graceful shutdown.</p>
        <p>Also: always pin your chromedriver version. Always.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="project-nav" data-animate>
    <div class="container project-nav-inner">
      <span></span>
      <a href="/projects/axto" class="btn-ghost">Next project →</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .project-hero { padding-top: 8rem; padding-bottom: 4rem; }
  .project-back {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }
  .project-back:hover { color: var(--text); }
  .project-cat {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 500;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .project-hero .accent-rule { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .project-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 0.95;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .project-tagline {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 36rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .project-links { display: flex; gap: 1rem; }

  .project-section { padding: 4rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .project-section-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
  }
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .project-section-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 12rem 1fr;
    }
  }
  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .project-section-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 14rem 1fr;
    }
  }

  .project-sidebar { }
  .project-sidebar-label {
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    display: block;
  }
  .project-techs { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.5rem; }
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .project-techs { flex-direction: column; }
  }

  .project-content h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }
  .project-content h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .project-content p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .project-content ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .project-content li {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  .project-content li strong { color: var(--text); }
  .project-content code {
    font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    background: var(--accent-light);
    padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .project-nav { padding: 3rem 0 6rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .project-nav-inner { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; }
</style>


